# [NETCONF](../wg/netconf.html)

## Summary

The NETCONF Working Group met at IETF 126. The session covered administrative updates, active working group drafts, and several non-chartered items. 

Key milestones included the publication of RFC 9918 (NETCONF over TLS 1.3) and RFC 9984 (UDP Client-Server). The group discussed progress on private candidate datastores, QUIC integration, list pagination, CBOR/HTTPS notifications, and YANG Push v2. There was also a strong show of hands supporting the adoption of a new work item on error list and identity registries.

---

## Key Discussion Points

### 1. Administration and Document Status
* **Presenter:** Kent Watsen and Per Hedeland
* **Slides:** [00-Chair Slides](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/126/materials/slides-126-netconf-chair-slides-02)
* **Discussion:**
  * **Published RFCs:** NETCONF over TLS 1.3 (RFC 9918) and UDP Client-Server (RFC 9984) have been officially published.
  * **YANG Library Augmented By Compiler Issue:** Per Hedeland raised an issue where reusing the grouping in `augmented-by` does not compile cleanly due to nested deprecated/non-deprecated status inheritance. Rob Wilton supported doing whatever is quickest to publish, suggesting resolving it at the RFC Editor level if it does not change semantics. Mahesh Jethandani agreed to recommend the necessary updates directly to the RFC Editor.
  * **UDP Notification:** Rob Wilton reported an open issue regarding DTLS implementation in `draft-ietf-netconf-udp-notif` involving an extra wrapping header. He will coordinate with the authors and chairs.

