### 2. HTTPS-based Transport for YANG Notifications
* **Presenter:** Mahesh Jethandani
* **Slides:** [01-YANG based HTTPS notification](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/126/materials/slides-126-netconf-yang-based-https-notification-01)
* **Draft:** [draft-ietf-netconf-https-notif](https://datatracker.ietf.org/id/draft-ietf-netconf-https-notif)
* **Discussion:** 
  * Mahesh presented updates from version -16, which resolved dependencies on the HTTP client-server draft.
  * Key updates include correcting media types to `application/yang-data+json` and `application/yang-data+xml`, formalizing the capability exchange using a YANG structure (RFC 8791), restructuring endpoints to use independent TLS configurations, and isolating legacy RFC 5277 support.
  * Qiufang Ma (shepherd) agreed to review the updates and refresh the shepherd write-up.

