### 5. NETCONF over QUIC
* **Presenter:** Weiqiang Cheng
* **Slides:** [04-NETCONF over QUIC](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/126/materials/slides-126-netconf-netconf-over-quic-00)
* **Draft:** [draft-ietf-netconf-over-quic](https://datatracker.ietf.org/id/draft-ietf-netconf-over-quic)
* **Discussion:**
  * **Call Home:** The presenter outlined two options: Option 1 (omit Call Home from this draft and defer it to a future document) and Option 2 (delay the draft until QUIC Call Home solutions are mature).
  * Kent Watsen (speaking as a contributor) noted that reverse QUIC is not on any immediate horizon, meaning Option 2 would delay the document indefinitely. Rob Wilton, Mahesh Jethandani, and Per Hedeland strongly supported Option 1 to get the base specification published.
  * Kent Watsen noted that current client-server drafts configure Call Home over QUIC, which might require future errata or updates. Rob Wilton advised against reopening those drafts at this stage.

