### 7. CBOR Encoding for HTTPS-based YANG Notifications Transport
* **Presenter:** Maher El-Aawar
* **Slides:** [06-CBOR Encoding for HTTPS-based YANG Notifications Transport](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/126/materials/slides-126-netconf-cbor-encoding-for-https-based-yang-notifications-transport-00)
* **Draft:** [draft-ietf-netconf-https-notif-cbor](https://datatracker.ietf.org/id/draft-ietf-netconf-https-notif-cbor)
* **Discussion:**
  * Maher presented alignment updates matching the parent HTTPS notification draft, including the correction of the media type to `application/yang-data+cbor`.
  * Alex Clemm suggested unbinding the notification messages from the underlying transport layer to allow reuse by other protocols like YANG Push v2. He proposed running WGLC for both the parent HTTPS draft and this CBOR draft concurrently as a cluster.
  * A participant noted that the examples currently use unallocated/invalid YANG SIDs. Alex Clemm pointed out that since the draft is stable and adopted, the authors should request early SID allocations from IANA.

