### 10. Requirements for Network State Exchange in Agent-Assisted Netops
* **Presenter:** Presenter (on behalf of the authors)
* **Slides:** [09-Requirements for Network State Exchange in Agent-Assisted Netops](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/126/materials/slides-126-netconf-requirements-for-network-state-exchange-in-agent-assisted-netops-00)
* **Discussion:**
  * The presenter introduced a non-chartered requirements draft exploring network state abstraction (e.g., using sketches) for AI/LLM network agents.
  * Kent Watsen and Mahesh Jethandani questioned whether the draft falls under the NETCONF charter. Thomas Graf noted that while the requirements might inform future YANG Push filtering needs, the draft's focus is broader. Rob Wilton expressed skepticism about standardizing requirements for rapidly evolving LLM technologies.
  * The presenter confirmed the draft will also be presented in the NMOP working group.

